answers.answerBody:
Hey Jess,


Yes indeed you can appear for examination in caravan but make sure that nobody is around because proctor ask for 360 degree view of caravan. 

Additionally there shouldn't be any electronic device near you like earphone, or any screen.    
I even appeared for examination in my SUV so I believe it shouldn't be a problem. 


Please close it if it answers your question.

Best of luck.

Cheers!

Amritansh Lal

Hi Jess

Microsoft Certification exams are available in several languages. However, candidates who must take the exam in English rather than in their native language can request an accommodation for additional time. Approval for extra time is provided on a case-by-case basis and needs to be requested in advance of the exam. This should be requested through the [accommodations process](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/learn/certifications/request-accommodations).

You may also contact the testing center for your accommodation request.

If you will take an exam from [PearsonVue](https://home.pearsonvue.com/microsoft/contact), you may reach out to their support through phone number or click on the link for chat option:

Contact: 855-542-6924, +1-952-905-7472 (toll)

[https://home.pearsonvue.com/microsoft/contact](https://home.pearsonvue.com/microsoft/contact)

For[PSI](https://psi-cdexp.zendesk.com/), you may create a ticket from this[link](https://psi-cdexp.zendesk.com/hc/requests/new?ticket_form_id=360001044112).For immediate response from PSI Candidate Care telephone numbers please contact:

US/Canada (toll free): 855.340.3887

US/Toll number for International Callers: 858.875.3686

For [Certiport Support Team](https://certiport.pearsonvue.com/Support/Support-for-test-candidates/Customer-service), you may refer to this link:

[https://certiport.pearsonvue.com/Contact-Us.aspx](https://certiport.pearsonvue.com/Contact-Us.aspx)

For reference, please visit [Request accommodations](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/learn/certifications/request-accommodations).

If this solves your problem, please indicate **Yes** to the question. If your inquiry was not fully resolved, [please post a new question](https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Ftrainingsupport.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fnewthread%3Fthreadtype%3DQuestions%26cancelurl%3D%252Fen-us%252Ftcmct%252Fforum%26forum%3Dtcmct%26filter%3D&data=02%7C01%7C%7Cd72b145fa45c4ef9faba08d8066cd244%7C1ca8bd943c974fc68955bad266b43f0b%7C0%7C0%7C637266411733360955&sdata=aHwSWMo31D8B14aPPdySQP4OgCZXmK5G1r2l6ClAoRY%3D&reserved=0) so we may continue in assisting you. This case will now be closed and locked.

Regards,
